stories.title: South Africa thrashed West Indies
stories.summary:
About 12 000 hometown fans cheered, whistled and waved flags
supporting the West Indies, but it was not enough to prevent South
Africa from wrapping up the Cable & Wireless One-Day International
cricket series yesterday at Kensington Oval

stories.title: South Africa clinch one-day series on back of Gibbs' brilliance
stories.summary:
A quite magnificent fifth one-day international century from Herschelle
Gibbs lead South Africa to a crushing seven-wicket win over a sloppy West
Indian side in the fifth one-day international at the Kensington Oval on
Wednesday
